      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "QUEST FOR STORM (8) is a smart dog who hit the ground running and cleared the ruck from the pinch draw to lead all the way to score (29.95) at Sandown in Grade 5 over 515m. Form at the trip sound including three wins. Won at his only start from this box. Well placed and can measure up. PAW HAZELTON (5) finished in the placings last time but could not have been more impressive before that in his sharp 25.35 win at Warrnambool over 450m. Has the ability and can find winning form again. MY DEAR FRIEND (1) has been beaten for early speed lately, last time finishing seventh (35.93) in a Grade 5 at The Meadows. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and two minor placings to his credit. One of the main contenders. MIDNIGHT THUNDER (3) warrants respect following a recent placing from the same draw.",
